Jonas Mushosho has been appointed to the board of Equity Group Holdings as a non-executive director replacing the retired Christopher Newson. Mushosho is expected to onboard his vast wealth of leadership experience having previously served in senior leadership positions in both the private and public sectors. He has served as the Chief Executive Officer at Old Mutual Zimbabwe between 2012 and 2019 during a period which he also doubled as the Groupâ€™s Managing Director for the Rest of Africa. Mushosho is currently a director at Brooks & Oracle, a council member at the Zimbabwe Open University and serves as a non-executive director at the Delta Corporation. He holds a bachelors of Accounting Science from the University of South Africa alongside an MBA from the University of Zimbabwe. Mushosho is also a chartered accountant and a fellow of the Institute of Chartered Secretaries and Administrators. Also Read: Video Of The Day: | CHASING HOPE | KEMRI undertaking stem cell research for treatment of Leishmaniasis